HEADWORD: haoma
<hw>haoma</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A leafless East Indian vine
(<spn>Sarcostemma acidum</spn>); its sour milky juice was formerly used
to make an intoxicating drink.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> soma, <spn>Sarcostemma acidum</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

